  "texts": [
    "However, this reliance can sometimes lead to superficial learning, where students apply solutions without fully understanding the logic behind them (Prather et al., 2024; Xue et al., 2024).",
    "On the other hand, more experienced students may tend to use AI tools in a complementary fashion as integrating them into their existing knowledge to enhance productivity and to solve complex problems (Xia et al., 2023).",
    "Different profiles in students' interaction behaviors can imply the need for personalized approaches to AI integration in educational context (Kim et al., 2024a; Stojanov et al., 2024).",
    "By recognizing and addressing the distinct ways in which students interact with AI, educators can better design instruction to meet individual needs, and maximize the educational benefits of using AI-driven tools like ChatGPT (Kim et al., 2024b).",
    "The integration of AI tools into educational settings can offer significant potential for enhancing learning outcomes and fostering student engagement."
  ],
